               <history>
                  <origin>
                     <origPlace>
                        <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/INS0071FBM">Faqādā Māryām</placeName>
                     </origPlace>
                     <origDate notBefore="1743" notAfter="1745">
                        <locus target="#98ra">98ra</locus>, etc.: ʾIyasu is mentioned as the
                        reigning king, Yoḥannǝs as the patriarch and another Yoḥannǝs as the
                        metropolitan. ʾIyasu II was king of Ethiopia in 1730-55; John XVII was
                        patriarch of Alexandria in 1727-45; Yoḥannǝs III was metropolitan of
                        Ethiopia in 1743-61.</origDate>
                  </origin>
               <provenance>According to Additio 2, ʾato Tänśǝʾa Krǝstos was the donor (s. also
                     supplication formulas, e. g., 13ra). Walatta
                     Māryām is mentioned in some supplication formulas(s. 75ra, 85vb, etc.).</provenance></history>
